  <p>
    To extend growing season Alberta gardeners rely on practical strategies:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Start warm-season crops as transplants.</li>
    <li>Use row cover in Alberta during early and late-season cold snaps.</li>
    <li>Employ low tunnels or greenhouse Alberta short season setups for added margin.</li>
    <li>Select shorter-maturity varieties.</li>
    <li>Monitor overnight lows closely in late summer.</li>
  </ul>

